WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.500
Finding local business leads one by one can eat hours.

00:00:07.500 --> 00:00:14.000
You search maps, open listings, copy details, check websites,
and still end up with a messy spreadsheet.

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:24.000
AiFetchly's Local Business Finder turns that manual work
into an organized search.

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:33.000
Choose Google Maps for global coverage,
or Yandex Maps for Russia, CIS markets, and Turkey.

00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:43.000
Open Local Business Finder from the left navigation.
In the Search tab, select your data source.

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:53.000
Enter the business type you want, like dentist,
Italian restaurant, plumber, or marketing agency.

00:00:53.000 --> 00:01:03.000
Next, enter the target location.
You can use a city, address, zip code, or wider region.

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:15.000
Now tune the search. Set the maximum results from 1 to 50
and include website URLs for outreach-ready records.

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:25.000
Turn on reviews only when you need extra detail.
Show Browser is usually off unless you are debugging.

00:01:25.000 --> 00:01:36.000
For Yandex searches, set language and region when needed.
You can also select an account and rotate proxies.

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:45.000
Click Start Search. AiFetchly runs in the background,
shows live progress, and lets you cancel if needed.

00:01:45.000 --> 00:01:52.000
When the search finishes, the table gives you names,
ratings, reviews, addresses, phones, websites, and map links.

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:58.000
Copy everything as JSON, export CSV for spreadsheets,
or export JSON for downstream tools.

00:01:58.000 --> 00:02:00.000
Local Business Finder gives you structured local leads,
ready for your next outreach step.
